content:
Identify and Segment Assets in Product Service Campaigns Easily

Swiftly curate lists of assets that you want to recall, audit, fix, or upgrade by creating actionable lists for product service campaigns. Specify sophisticated filter conditions or use Data Cloud segments to group assets that you want to include in actionable lists. With a single click, add items from actionable lists to product service campaigns. Set list priorities, sort list orders, customize details, and assign lists to service agents for engagement initiatives and service activities.

This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions with Manufacturing Cloud. The user interface of this product is available in English only and may not be fully supported in other languages.

Users who have the Actionable Segmentation, Query for Data Pipelines, and Product Service Campaign permission sets can use this feature.

Manufacturers store rich data on a large number of assets. Itâ€™s cumbersome to identify faulty assets and individually add them to product service campaigns. Service managers can identify and add a large number of assets to product service campaigns easily by using actionable lists.

On a Product Service Campaign record page, click Create Actionable List. Create an actionable list and click Add to Service Campaign.
title: Easy Asset Management for Manufacturing Cloud
